external_knowledge:
- 'DOI' stands for Digital Object Identifier and is a unique alphanumeric string assigned to a digital object (e.g., journal article, dataset);
- 'ORCID' stands for Open Researcher and Contributor ID and is a unique identifier for researchers and contributors;
- Citation count refers to the number of times a publication is cited by other publications;
- A PDF link typically points to a Portable Document Format version of the publication.

sql:
SELECT title
FROM publications
WHERE citation_count = (
  SELECT MAX(citation_count)
  FROM publications
);

SELECT DISTINCT year 
FROM publications 
WHERE status = 'Published' AND citation_count > 10;
